title: For Sale:  Colt SAA - 1902 - 1st Gen - 4-3/4" bbl
postcontent:
1st gen Colt SAA, in .32WCF.  Serial number is 226xxx.  Very little original bluing left; maybe 10%.  There isn't any rust, its just so old that the case blue finish on the frame and hammer is gone, as is the bluing on the barrel and other pieces.  Action is tight and timed well, 4 good clicks on the hammer.  All serial numbered parts match, the rifling is crisp and the bore is shiny; all chambers in the cylinder are shiny, with no visible pitting.  Grips are original, with noticeable wear from a right handed shooter.  Small crack at the bottom of the left grip, but it hasn't fractured to the outside yet.  Small 'bushing', made from the same material as the grips, sits between them where the grip screw pulls them tight.  Appears to be original, but I haven't seen anything like it from Colt before.

Original base pin was bent and mauled pretty badly by vise grips; replacement is in now, from a 1904 SAA.  Original will be included, in case you want to try to repair it & use it instead.  Ejector seems to have had a 'field repair' done on it; seems to be the original piece, but it broke and appears to have been welded back on.  These things were tools, back in the day, and they were often treated that way.

I had a local SASS/Colt SAA guru smoke it over pretty good, and while inside it, there were a couple of hiccups...the bolt was tweaked a little, and it broke when he was trying to bend it back into place; it was replaced and fitted properly.  The sear and bolt spring snapped during reassembly; it was replaced.  The base pin latch assembly was missing from the gun, he used the one from his 1904 piece.  

I have the Colt Letter, verifying that the gun was shipped to Townley Metal and Hardware Company, Kansas City, MO, in May of 1902.  The letter will go with the revolver when it ships.  I have MANY pictures of the revolver and can provide them upon request, or take specific pics of whatever you want to see.

Blue Book puts the value at $2,000-$4,000; at the NRA show in Houston this year, I spoke with several Colt Collectors & dealers, and got values from $1,500 to $5,000, with offers from $1,200 to $2,000 (they 'wanted a little room' so they could make some money on it).

I'd like to get $3,500 for it.  Shipped to your FFL or FTF in central NC.  Price is negotiable, but lowball offers will be rejected out of hand.

title: For Sale:  Primary Weapon Systems MK116 Mod 1 16" PWS MK 1
postcontent:
This is a brand new Primary Weapon Systems AR-15 semi-automatic rifle with a high performance .223 Wylde chamber. .223 Wylde is a proprietary rifle cartridge chamber with the same external dimensions and lead angle as found in the the military 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and the 0.2240 inch freebore diameter as found in the civilian SAAMI .223 Remington cartridge. The .223 Wylde hybrid chamber was designed to exploit the accuracy advantages of the .223 Remington chambering without pressure problems or compromising the functional reliability of semi automatic weapons like the AR-15 family when using 5.56×45mm NATO military ammunition.

The shortest of the non-NFA models with a removable muzzle device, the PWS MK116 Rifle is a crowd favorite. The MK116 is designed for a multitude of uses and retains lethal capability out to 500 meters with varying types of ammunition and boasts a PWS FSC556 muzzle device. The 16" barrel features a versatile 1:8" twist rate, offering stabilization of the widest ranges of bullet weights available.

Understanding the importance of an ultra-reliable package that is light as possible, mil-spec forgings are used for the upper and lower receiver. Additional features include the BCM GUNFIGHTER charging handle, the PWS enhanced buffer tube and an ALG Defense QMS trigger. The rifle is rounded out with industry leading features such as Magpul MOE grip, MOE stock, and MBUS sights

title: For Sale:  Bersa Thunder 380, NIB, Warranty
postcontent:
Last one left!

Bersa Thunder is one of the many derivatives of Walther PPK design. Since the supply of the military surplus Makarovs and CZ 82s have dwindled, Bersa has become the most economical way to own a gun similar to that owned by Agent 007 for half the price, and no loss in accuracy.

James Bong, as it happens, knew what he was doing when it came to the choice of firearms. 380 ACP is the most powerful Western caliber that is practical with a blowback action. Since in a blowback gun the barrel does not move, the gun is surprisingly accurate for its size, and has a very manageable recoil.

For a more detailed review see here: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/BersaThunder380.aspx

The gun is new as shipped from the distributor. You will be the first retail owner.

FAQ - PLEASE READ! I am not going to respond to questions that are covered here!

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site, by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5%

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. Insured Priority Mail shipping for this gun will be $20.

title: For Sale:  Modified Yugo sks - Super Pig Hunter ! - $400
postcontent:
Hi, I have a Yugo SKS for sale.  I picked this up in a trade about two years ago.  The gun was as issued, all numbers matched, however, the front sight and Grenade launcher/Flash had been cut off.  

The Yugo barrel is turned to accept the front sight block and the barrel was hand cut right past the sight block in the groove left from the turning.  The cut was nicely done, button crowned and properly lapped, however, the gun wasn't cycling well due to pressure/gas block issues.  I stick measured the barrel per ATF reg. and it is 17 and3/8 inches long.  

I replaced the original on/off adjustable Yugo gas block with a Murray's Stainless steel fixed block, and that totally solved the gas/cycle issue.  I also upgraded to a Tapco stock with an ATI adjustable buttstock.  

The gun comes with a Tru-Glo 2x red dot, Tapco Mag, and plastic gun case, along with the original stock and fixed mag.  I also have a bolt on front sight and flash, if you want.

This gun is now a fun, light, carbine that is great for the Pig!!  I have always been able to reliably cycle the 156g Softpoints, and the gun is accurate for an SKS.  Usual 50 yard groups are 1-2 inch.  

I am pulling together cash for a new build so trading is not my first option.  I do work out of town and I am only available on Sat 8am-9pm or Sunday 8am-5pm.  Please Email contact info and I will respond!  Thanks seven seven 5v354three seven 9 seven

title: For Sale/Trade:  Extremely rare WW2 German Battlefield photo album Alligtator skinned leather
postcontent:
Very rare one of a kind piece of ww2 history
 Original photographs from ww2
 You simply can not go somewhere and buy one of these like a lot of military collectibles
 I am relinquishing parts of my ww2 collection so that others may enjoy them.
 This is an alligator skinned leather photo album from the tours of the very first anti aircraft/anti tank unit that Germany created for world war two
 I Flak/Regt 5 
 Alligator skin/leather is in really good shape for it's age and you have to see it to appreciate it.It has a leather strip tied that is binding the pages to the album.Pages are in great shape and still have the onion paper dividers so the pictures don't stick together.
 I have all of the photos removed so they can be viewed without man handling the album it self.(almost 100 pictures)
 There were only six of these units created and they never existed before ww2.This was the very first unit created and remained in service the longest (unit created 10 January,1935 and remained in service until the end of the war in 1945)
 http://www.ww2.dk/ground/flak/flargt5.html
 http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flak_corps 
 This album chronicles the units tours through the war.

 Some of the pictures are nicely captioned and dated and include pictures of bombed and burnt out vehicles,artillery,soldiers digging graves and trenches,the huge range finders they used and also a lot of candid shots of the soldiers smiling and having fun playing soccer in the dirt,stacks of wine bottles,playing music ,hanging out in their field tents,etc

 Anyway,i have decided to let this piece go.This is a must have for anybody who is a ww2 buff.Like I said before,this is simply not something you can go out and buy and there will NEVER be another one

 I have added a few pictures here but can take and email more although it would be best to meet and let you see it in person. 
 Will trade for:
 Firearms,modern firearms,c&r,hunting rifles,pistols.......will entertain all other trades 
Will trade for:
what do you have?prefer firearms and related items

A nice turkish mauser, has great trigger and is very accurate. Bore in good shape. Crown is clean, no dings. Numbers don't match, but I don't think I have ever seen a turkish mauser with matching numbers. This rifle has been tested out to 100 yards and shoots small groups. This is an Ankara, manufactured/stamped 1945.

There is a stock repair on the right side, which has been neatly done. The stock is sound and there are no issues with the repair, i.e. it's all solid as a rock.

Everything functions well and the rifle is reliable.

Bluing probably about 70-80%.

It's a clean, accurate gun, with a great trigger. If you have never shoot a mauser, I believe you may be in for a treat. This is just a little more than the price of a mosin nagant, but it's street's ahead in terms of quality, accuracy and function. Bolts on mosins are really shiity and sticky, bolts on mausers have been copied by all great modern day manufacturers. This rifle has a smooth bolt and bullets cycle effortlessly.  This represents a better purchase than a mosin, if you were looking for a better milsurp rifle.
